-- Mexican Remittances Climbed 12% in May From Year Earlier to $2.13 Billion
-- Jens Erik Gould
-- 2010-07-01T14:03:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/mexican-remittances-climbed-12-in-may-from-year-earlier-to-2-13-billion.html

          
          
             Mexican remittances rose 12 percent
in May from a year earlier.  
 Money sent from workers living outside Mexico climbed to
$2.13 billion in May from $1.9 billion in the same month a year
earlier, the central bank  said  today on its website.  
